reviews.review_text:
Really nice recording and hot show !  Wow,  what a nice sounding source and a well played show too!  I "think" I had a copy of this source on DAT back in the day but it may have been a 1st gen?  However,  a big thanks to CM and co. for the fresh transfer.  There's no doubt that the transfers seem to get better as the technology advances IF you can find the master source!  I like the sound of the Nak 300s shotguns with the Nak 100 cardiod mics ; I think the Nak 3 channel mixers were very cool idea for field recording.  

A great 1st set with a rare 1st "I Need a Miracle" and almost a pure rock and roll set with no real psychedelic jams like a Birdsong or Let it Grow.  The second set is also rocking but features a rare second treat of "High Time"  But, Look Out! It's a really nice Estimated > Eyes with a really cool vocal effects on Weir with audience gasps and then Phil throws the famous bombs before settling into Eyes intro.  The post space is rocking too with a impromptu Lovelight as if the band didn't have enough time to leave stage for an encore.  Yes,  Garcia has some gravel vocals but when Jerry doesn't sing top notch; he plays ALOT of guitar with verve!  This is worth a download a nice upfront full sound that is relatively balanced with a stereo image.

My first tape This may be the best source. Great stereo separation and levels, no hiss.

First full show I had passed to me when I was 14 (1987?) 
China/Rider wails. High Time a treat. Fragile China Doll out of space is a gem. Get it!
